{{Infobox football biography | playername = Yasuyuki Konno | image = [[File:Yasuyuki Konno - 2.jpg|200px]] | fullname = Yasuyuki Konno | dateofbirth = {{birth date and age|1983|1|25}} | cityofbirth = [[Sendai, Miyagi]] | countryofbirth = [[Japan]] | height = {{height|ft=5|in=10}} | youthyears1 = 1998-2000| youthclubs1 = TÅhoku High School | currentclub = [[F.C. Tokyo]] | clubnumber = 6 | position = [[Midfielder]], [[Defender]] | years1 = 2001&ndash;2003 |clubs1 = [[Consadole Sapporo]] |caps1 = 65 |goals1 = 2 | years2 = 2004&ndash; |clubs2 = [[F.C. Tokyo]] |caps2 = 221 |goals2 = 32 | nationalyears1 = 2002&ndash;2003 | nationalyears2 = 2004 | nationalyears3 = 2005&ndash; | nationalteam1 = [[Japan national football team|Japan U-20]] | nationalteam2 = [[Japan national football team|Japan U-23]] | nationalteam3 = [[Japan national football team|Japan]] | nationalcaps1 = 13 | nationalcaps2 = 9 | nationalcaps3 = 47 | nationalgoals1 = 4 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | pcupdate = 04 December 2010 | ntupdate = 1 June 2011 }} {{Nihongo|'''Yasuyuki Konno'''|ä»é æ³°å¹¸|Konno Yasuyuki|born January 25, 1983 in [[Sendai, Miyagi|Sendai]], [[Japan]]}} is a Japanese [[football (soccer)|football]] player who plays for [[F.C. Tokyo]] in Japan's professional [[J. League]].
He was part of the Japanese [[Football at the 2004 Summer Olympics|2004 Olympic football]] team, which finished fourth in group B, below group winners [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]], [[Italy national football team|Italy]] and [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]].
He also capped for Japan U-20 team at the [[2003 FIFA World Youth Championship]].
On August 3, 2005, he made his senior national team debut in an [[East Asian Cup 2005|East Asian Cup]] match against [[China national football team|China]].
